						               													<description>The Last Drifters&amp;#10;These rules are meant for any small scale cars made by any manufacturer (as long as both forces are of a similar scale). &amp;#10;The vehicles used as examples in these rules are cheap converted children's cars that you can find in most toy shops, and the games are aimed at using around two to three vehicles per side for a normal game of maybe an hour or so. The system can cope with more vehicles per side but these games would take longer to play.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The rules cover a selection of vehicles that you would expect to find in a post apocalyptic world, from fast motorbikes all the way up to heavy battle trucks. The rules also cover many different weapons and armour that these vehicles could possibly carry.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;These rules also contain a selection of ways to play, plus a section containing a few scenarios like:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     Resting Beside The Road - a couple of drifters are taking a rest beside the road when they hear ganger motorbikes!&amp;#10;     Find The Lady - a VIP is travelling in one of the cars can you get them to safety?&amp;#10;     Plus a few others.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;At the back of these rules you will find a print out section with the data sheets for all the basic&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Vehicles and some blank ones so that you can build your own vehicles. You will also find all of the counters for you to use in your games.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
